<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-70] missing space in lctldl command line example. </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-70</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.html#lustremaintenance&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.html#lustremaintenance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   lctldl|grep &quot; osc &quot;&lt;br/&gt;
       ^&lt;br/&gt;
There should be a space here. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It also says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is sample lctl dl | grep&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which isn&apos;t particularly good English, and also misses out the &quot; osc &quot; from the line above. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chris&lt;/p&gt;</description>
